methods.build:
Use to start the construction of a Table Supplier.

:param sourceTable: (io.deephaven.engine.table.Table) - the source table
:return: (io.deephaven.engine.table.Table) a Proxy that will supply a table
methods.complete:
Sets a Table Supplier to be complete. This means that the supplier will generate a table the next time a filter
 operation is called. This method has no affect on Tables that are not suppliers.

:param maybeSupplier: (io.deephaven.engine.table.Table) - a Table that may be a supplier
:return: (io.deephaven.engine.table.Table) a completed Supplier or unaltered Table
methods.getAppliedEmptyTable:
Gets an empty version of the supplied table with all current operations applied to it. If the Table is not a
 Table Supplier then this will return the table unaltered.

:param maybeSupplier: (io.deephaven.engine.table.Table) - a Table that may be a supplier
:return: (io.deephaven.engine.table.Table) an applied empty table or an unaltered table
methods.invoke:
:param proxy: java.lang.Object
:param method: java.lang.reflect.Method
:param args: java.lang.Object[]
:return: java.lang.Object

text:
TableSupplier creates a Proxy to a Table with a list of Table operations to be applied when a filter method is
 called.
